                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d571">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 337.11/216</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Gonzales</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-02T21:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 2, 1917, 9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s March 1, 7 p.m. According to wireless from the Commander of U. S. S.
                        <hi rend="italic">Eagle</hi>, Central Senado, Camaguey Province, burned.
                    Government information is that Santa Lucia, Oriente Province, and Por Fuerza,
                    Matanzas Province, all right. Santa Maria, Oriente Province, is in rebel zone
                    and no information procurable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
